  "prompt": "Is money laundering subject to legal prosecution?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is definitely subject to legal prosecution in most countries around the world. It is a serious crime with severe penalties, including:\n\n*   **Imprisonment:** Often lengthy prison sentences.\n*   **Fines:** Significant financial penalties.\n*   **Asset Forfeiture:** The seizure of assets involved in or derived from the illegal activity.\n*   **Other Penalties:** These can include restrictions on financial activities, loss of professional licenses, and reputational damage.\n\nLaws and regulations against money laundering are in place at both the national and international levels to combat organized crime, terrorism financing, and other illicit activities. These laws are designed to prevent criminals from concealing the origins of their ill-gotten gains and integrating them into the legitimate financial system.",
